text: The Bonhoeffer Botanical Gardens are a botanical garden located north of Seattle. They are named in honor of Dietrich Bonhoeffer, a Lutheran pastor and scholar, who was executed in April, 1945, in Nazi Germany's Flossenburg concentration camp. The garden contains native plants of the Pacific Northwest. ==References== ==External links== * Official website Category:Botanical gardens in Washington (state) Category:Lutheran churches in Washington (state)
